#TBT to when WHO-TV surprised Annette Purdy (WHS Science Teacher) with a Golden Apple Award earlier this year!!! She was nominated by four WHS students, and if you had a chance to see Annette in action, you know this was a well-deserved award.

The students' nomination talked about how she engaged students in learning through projects and collaboration with scientists, health care providers and naturalists in the field. The students commented about how she had high expectations for their learning, yet helped students grasp difficult concepts. They said her students felt welcomed and cared for in her classroom. They went on to say that many students find their passion in science because of the experiences Annette provided to them in class.

And a huge congratulations to Annette on her recent retirement! We are so proud of you!!!

The following is a statement from the Iowa Department of Public Health.

The is no delay for the requirements for immunizations to begin the school year.

Dr.s Offices are taking appointments now. Please consider getting this important task done now.

Iowa Immunization Program has been in consultation with health care providers, other states, the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC), and currently does not plan to delay or suspend immunization requirements for the 2020-21 school year. In order to attend school or licensed child care for the 2020-21 school year, the child needs a valid Iowa Department of Public Health-Certificate of Immunization, Provisional Certificate of Immunization, or Certificate of Immunization Exemption.
